                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14467333" author="jwb" created="Wed, 5 Aug 2009 19:02:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve refactored Sql.java to eliminate some duplicated code as well as make the synchronization consistent.  Unfortunately, I don&apos;t have time to develop a test case that will reliably fail due to the current, improper synchronized blocks.  In particular, making a unit test that will reliably fail due to the current bug and will reliably succeed with the correction is a significant task.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to use this refactored version as a the basis for an enhancement to allow subclasses to gain access to the ResultSet (cursor) returned by JDBC.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PS, I&apos;d like my JIRA ID to be on the user list so that I can own the issues.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467301" author="blackdrag" created="Wed, 5 Aug 2009 19:22:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;is it really ok to remove those &quot;configure&quot; calls?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467422" author="jwb" created="Wed, 5 Aug 2009 19:28:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The calls to configure are still made. The refactoring moved configure() to 2 common methods so they are made from 2 methods rather than ~8.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14478643" author="paulk" created="Thu, 6 Aug 2009 08:27:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the Patch! Added to trunk - pending merge onto 1_6_X branch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;P.S. When you submit new issues, e.g. suggested cursor enhancement, you will automatically be listed as the Reporter for the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467321" author="jwb" created="Thu, 6 Aug 2009 22:33:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One of the thread-safety measures in my patch was dropped: configure(Statement) calls through the field value that could be set null after it&apos;s tested and cause NPE.  An optimizing compiler may avoid this situation since the field is not volatile, but the change I proposed seems to be an improvement.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14478625" author="paulk" created="Thu, 6 Aug 2009 23:16:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My bad. Fixing now and I&apos;ll make it more obvious too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14478608" author="paulk" created="Fri, 7 Aug 2009 02:14:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Now added to 1_6_X branch and tweaked as per recent comment&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
